#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:35
#, no-c-format
msgid "Introduction"
msgstr "Intangiriro"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:37
#, fuzzy, no-c-format
msgid ""
"&konqueror; offers some features to enhance your browsing experience. One "
"such feature is <emphasis>Web Shortcuts</emphasis>."
msgstr ""
"&konqueror; Ibiranga Kuri Gushakisha . Ikiranga ni <emphasis> </emphasis> . "

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:40
#, fuzzy, no-c-format
msgid ""
"You may already have noticed that &kde; is very Internet friendly. For "
"example, you can click on the <guimenuitem>Run</guimenuitem> menu item or "
"type the keyboard shortcut assigned to that command (<keycombo action=\"simul"
"\">&Alt;<keycap>F2</keycap></keycombo> or <keycombo action=\"simul\">&Alt;"
"&Space;</keycombo>, unless you have changed it) and type in a &URI;."
msgstr ""
"Gicurasi &kde; ni . Urugero: , Kanda ku i <guimenuitem> </guimenuitem> "
"Ibikubiyemo Ikintu Cyangwa Ubwoko: i Mwandikisho Iy'ibusamo Kuri command "
"( <keycombo action=\"simul\"> <keycap> </keycap> <keycap> </keycap> </"
"keycombo> , Byahinduwe ) na Ubwoko: in A <acronym> </acronym> . "

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:46
#, fuzzy, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Uniform Resource Identifier. A standardized way of referring to a resource "
"such as a file on your computer, a World Wide Web address, an email address, "
"&etc;"
msgstr ""
". A Bya Kuri A Ibikorana: Nka A Idosiye ku , A Aderesi: , Imeli Aderesi: , "
"<abbrev> ... "

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:50
#, fuzzy, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Web shortcuts, on the other hand, let you come up with new pseudo &URL; "
"schemes, or shortcuts, that basically let you <emphasis>parameterize</"
"emphasis> commonly used &URI;s. For example, if you like the Google search "
"engine, you can configure &kde; so that a pseudo &URL; scheme like "
"<emphasis>gg</emphasis> will trigger a search on Google. This way, typing "
"<userinput>gg:<replaceable>my query</replaceable></userinput> will search "
"for <replaceable>my query</replaceable> on Google."
msgstr ""
"Amahinanzira , ku i Ikindi , Hejuru Na: Gishya <acronym> </acronym> , "
"Cyangwa Amahinanzira , <emphasis> </emphasis> Byakoreshejwe <acronym> </"
"acronym> S . Urugero: , NIBA nka i Shakisha , Kugena Imiterere MukusanyaKDE "
"A <acronym> </acronym> Igishusho nka <emphasis> </emphasis> Imbarutso A "
"Shakisha ku . , Kwandika :$1 <userinput> : <replaceable> Ikibazo # </"
"replaceable> </userinput> Shakisha ya:  <replaceable> Ikibazo # </"
"replaceable> ku . "

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:60
#, fuzzy, no-c-format
msgid ""
"One can see why we call these pseudo &URL; schemes. They are used like a "
"&URL; scheme, but the input is not properly &URL; encoded, so one will type "
"<userinput>google:kde apps</userinput> and not <userinput>google:kde+apps</"
"userinput>."
msgstr ""
"Twebwe <acronym> </acronym> . Byakoreshejwe nka A <acronym> </acronym> "
"Igishusho , i Iyinjiza ni OYA <acronym> </acronym> , Rimwe Ubwoko: "
"<userinput> google : kde </userinput> na OYA <userinput> google : kde + </"
"userinput> . "

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:66
#, fuzzy, no-c-format
msgid ""
"You can use web shortcuts wherever you would normally use &URI;s. Shortcuts "
"for several search engines should already be configured on your system, but "
"you can add new keywords, and change or delete existing ones in this module."
msgstr ""
"Koresha Urubuga Amahinanzira Koresha <acronym> </acronym> S . ya:  Shakisha "
"ku Sisitemu , &Ongera Gishya Amagambo-shingiro , na Guhindura... Cyangwa "
"Gusiba in i Biteye imbere Gushakisha Igenzura Modire . "

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:76
#, no-c-format
msgid "Web Search Keywords"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:78
#, fuzzy, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The descriptive names of defined web shortcuts are shown in a list box. As "
"with other lists in &kde;, you can click on a column heading to toggle the "
"sort order between ascending and descending, and you can resize the columns."
msgstr ""
"Amazina Bya Urubuga Amahinanzira in A . Na: Ikindi Intonde in &kde; , Kanda "
"ku A Inkingi Umutwempangano Kuri Mukomatanya i Ishungura Itondekanya hagati "
"ikijyejuru na ikijyepfo , na Ihindurangero %O i Inkingi: . "

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:83
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"At the bottom of the list the option <guilabel>Enable Web search keywords</"
"guilabel> has to be checked to enable this feature. Use the buttons on the "
"right to create, modify or delete shortcuts."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:87
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"If <guilabel>Use preferred keywords only</guilabel> is checked, only "
"keywords marked as preferred in the second column of the list are used in "
"places where only a few select shortcuts can be shown at one time."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:93
#, no-c-format
msgid "Below the list you find two additional options:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: guilabel
#: index.docbook:95
#, fuzzy, no-c-format
msgid "Default Web search keyword:"
msgstr "Urubuga Amahinanzira "

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:97
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Select the search engine to use for input boxes that provide automatic "
"lookup services when you type in normal words and phrases instead of a "
"&URL;. To disable this feature select <guilabel>None</guilabel> from the "
"list."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: guilabel
#: index.docbook:102
#, no-c-format
msgid "Keyword delimiter:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:104
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Choose the delimiter that separates the keyword from the phrase or word to "
"be searched."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:109
#, fuzzy, no-c-format
msgid ""
"If you double-click on a specific entry in the list of defined search "
"providers or click the <guibutton>Change...</guibutton> button, the details "
"for that entry are shown in a popup dialog. In addition to the descriptive "
"name for the item, you can also see the &URI; which is used, as well as the "
"associated shortcuts which you can type anywhere in &kde; where &URI;s are "
"expected. A given search provider can have multiple shortcuts, each "
"separated by a comma."
msgstr ""
"MAHARAKUBIRI - Kanda ku A Icyinjijwe in i Urutonde Bya Shakisha , i "
"Birambuye ya:  Icyinjijwe in A Byirambuye Ikiganiro . Guteranya + Kuri i "
"Izina: ya:  i Ikintu , i <acronym> </acronym> ni Byakoreshejwe , Nka Nka i "
"Amahinanzira Ubwoko: Aho ariho hose in &kde; <acronym> </acronym> S "
"Ikitezwe: $(ARG1) . A Shakisha Igikubo Amahinanzira , ku A akitso . "

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:118
#, fuzzy, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The text boxes are used not only for displaying information about an item in "
"the list of web shortcuts, but also for modifying or adding new items."
msgstr ""
"Umwandiko Byakoreshejwe OYA ya:  Ibisobanuro: Bigyanye Ikintu in i Urutonde "
"Bya Urubuga Amahinanzira , ya:  Cyangwa Wongera Gishya Ibigize . "

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:122
#, fuzzy, no-c-format
msgid ""
"You can change the contents of either the <guilabel>Shortcut URL:</guilabel> "
"or the <guilabel>Shortcuts:</guilabel> text box. Click <guibutton>OK</"
"guibutton> to save your changes or <guibutton>Cancel</guibutton> to exit the "
"dialog with no changes."
msgstr ""
"Guhindura... i Ibigize Bya i <guilabel> </guilabel> Cyangwa i <guilabel> </"
"guilabel> Umwandiko Agasanduku . <guibutton> </guibutton> Kuri Kubika "
"Amahinduka Cyangwa <guibutton> </guibutton> Kuri &Kuvamo i Ikiganiro Na: Oya "
"Amahinduka . "

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:128
#, fuzzy, no-c-format
msgid ""
"If you examine the contents of the <guilabel>Shortcut URL:</guilabel> text "
"box, you will find that most, if not all of the entries have a <option>\\{@}"
"</option> in them. This sequence of four characters acts as a parameter, "
"which is to say that they are replaced by whatever you happen to type after "
"the colon character that is between a shortcut and its parameter. To add "
"this query placeholder to a shortcut &URL;, click on the button at the right "
"of the text box. Let's consider some examples to clarify how to use web "
"shortcuts."
msgstr ""
"i Ibigize Bya i <guilabel> </guilabel> Umwandiko Agasanduku , Gushaka , NIBA "
"OYA Byose Bya i Ibyinjijwe A <option> \\{ @ } </option> in . Bya Kabiri "
"Inyuguti Nka A Ikintu , ni Kuri ku Kuri Ubwoko: Nyuma i Utudomo tubiri "
"Inyuguti: ni hagati A Iy'ibusamo na Ikintu . Ingero Kuri iyi . "

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:137
#, fuzzy, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Suppose that the &URI; is <userinput>https://www.google.com/search?q=\\{@}</"
"userinput>, and <userinput>gg</userinput> is a shortcut to this &URI;. Then, "
"typing <userinput>gg:<replaceable>alpha</replaceable></userinput> is "
"equivalent to <userinput>https://www.google.com/search?q=<replaceable>alpha</"
"replaceable></userinput>. You could type anything after the <userinput>:</"
"userinput> character; whatever you have typed simply replaces the <option>"
"\\{@}</option> characters, after being converted to the appropriate "
"character set for the search provider and then properly &URL;-encoded. Only "
"the <option>\\{@}</option> part of the search &URI; is touched, the rest of "
"it is supposed to be properly &URL;-encoded already and is left as is."
msgstr "google. comsearch. google. comsearch."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:153
#, fuzzy, no-c-format
msgid ""
"You can also have shortcuts without parameters. Suppose the &URI; was "
"<emphasis>file:/home/me/mydocs/calligra/words</emphasis> and the shortcut "
"was <emphasis>mywords</emphasis>. Then, typing <userinput>mywords:</"
"userinput> is the same as typing the complete &URI;. Note that there is "
"nothing after the colon when typing the shortcut, but the colon is still "
"required in order for the shortcut to be recognized as such."
msgstr ""
"Amahinanzira Ibigenga . i <acronym> </acronym> <emphasis> Idosiye : /"
"Home ////</emphasis> na i Iy'ibusamo <emphasis> </emphasis> . , Kwandika :$1 "
"<userinput> : </userinput> ni i Nka Kwandika :$1 i Byuzuye <acronym> </"
"acronym> . icyitonderwa ni Nta na kimwe Nyuma i Utudomo tubiri Ryari: "
"Kwandika :$1 i Iy'ibusamo , i Utudomo tubiri ni Bya ngombwa in Itondekanya "
"ya:  i Iy'ibusamo Kuri Nka . "

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:162
#, fuzzy, no-c-format
msgid ""
"By now, you will have understood that even though these shortcuts are called "
"web shortcuts, they really are shortcuts to parameterized &URI;s, which can "
"point not only to web sites like search engines but also to anything else "
"that can be pointed to by a &URI;. Web shortcuts are a very powerful feature "
"of navigation in &kde;."
msgstr ""
"NONEAHA , ATARIIGIHARWE Amahinanzira Urubuga Amahinanzira , Amahinanzira "
"Kuri <acronym> </acronym> S , Akadomo OYA Kuri Urubuga nka Shakisha Kuri "
"Ikindi Kuri ku A <acronym> </acronym> . Amahinanzira A Ikiranga Bya Ibuganya "
"in &kde; . "

